---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Dataset Licence · Fractune"
  description="Read the dataset licence for Fractune, including permitted academic and journalistic uses, attribution rules, and restrictions on redistribution and AI training."
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <h1>Dataset Licence</h1>
      <p class="caption">Last updated: May 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Dataset Licence forms part of the Fractune Terms &amp; Conditions
        and governs how you may use the public Fractune dataset of architectural
        fluency readings. For legal details and additional rights and
        obligations, please also read our full
        <a href="/terms">Terms &amp; Conditions</a> and
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What the Dataset Contains</h2>
      <p>The Fractune public dataset (the "Dataset") consists of:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Reading metrics</strong>, for each contributed analysis: the
          composite Architectural Fluency F, the four dimension sub-scores
          (F_fractal, F_rhythm, F_chromatic, F_structure), confidence,
          fractal dimension D, lacunarity Λ, edge-orientation entropy
          H<sub>θ</sub>, curvature ratio κ, value contrast Δ_L, visual balance
          B, hierarchical scaling Σ_h, solid/void ratio V, spectral slope β,
          rhythm strengths R<sub>h</sub>/R<sub>v</sub>, fenestration
          regularity R<sub>w</sub>, harmony type, and quality / perspective
          status.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Optional location and orientation</strong>, latitude,
          longitude, camera heading, and pitch, when the contributor enabled
          location sharing for the reading.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Optional building metadata</strong>, name, address,
          architect, style, type, construction year, and a metadata source
          tag, when the contributor enriched the reading.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Optional face-redacted thumbnail</strong>, when the
          contributor consented to image donation. Faces are detected and
          blurred on the contributor's device before upload.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Anonymous contributor ID</strong>, a randomly generated
          UUID. It cannot be reversed to identify a person.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Timestamps and app/model versions</strong>, for scientific
          reproducibility.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The Dataset is browsable at
        <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.
        A public read-only API is not currently offered; researchers who
        need programmatic access can request it under
        <a href="#research-partnerships">Research Partnerships</a> below.
      </p>

      <h2>Licence Grant</h2>
      <p>
        Subject to your continuous compliance with this Dataset Licence and the
        Terms &amp; Conditions, you are granted a
        <strong>limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable licence</strong>
        to access and use the Dataset for the permitted purposes described
        below. No ownership of the Dataset, the underlying readings, or the
        derived metrics is transferred to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Permitted Uses</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Academic and scientific research:</strong> using the Dataset
          in research projects, peer-reviewed publications, theses, and
          academic conference work, provided proper attribution is given (see
          below).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Education and personal study:</strong> exploring the Dataset
          to study fractal geometry, perceptual aesthetics, architectural
          composition, and related fields. Citing individual readings in
          coursework or lectures is permitted.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Architectural and urban planning analysis:</strong> using the
          Dataset to inform design decisions, comparative studies of
          neighbourhoods or eras, and built-environment assessments, including
          for client work, provided you do not redistribute the Dataset itself.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Journalism and public-interest reporting:</strong>
          referencing or visualising readings in news articles, reports, and
          public-interest publications, with attribution.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Attribution</h2>
      <p>
        When publishing research, analysis, visualisations, or reports based
        on data from the Fractune Dataset, you must credit the source as
        <strong>"Fractune (fractune.dk)"</strong> and, where applicable, cite
        the Dataset with a link to
        <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.
        For academic citation, use the format on the
        <a href="/research">Research</a> page.
      </p>

      <h2>Restrictions</h2>
